The paper deals with inference in large-scale hybrid systems, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of variational models and iid random variables suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The application of the algorithm to environmental engineering suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY), while the use of probability relational models suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB).
